subject: Re: [junit] assertEquals
msgSnippet: This seems highly unlikely.  Two objects pointing to the same reference are absolutely equal.  Are you sure you copied the message properly? -jason ... =====
messageBody:
This seems highly unlikely. Two objects pointing to the same reference are
absolutely equal. Are you sure you copied the message properly?

-jason

--- benjamin@... wrote:
> Hello,
> I am testing a EJB with an assertEquals and I get the following:
>
> junit.framework.AssertionFailedError: Wrong country
> expected:<ethenticate/Country:com.notuskey.persistence.whoWhere.Countr
> yPK@e0> but
> was:<ethenticate/Country:com.notuskey.persistence.whoWhere.CountryPK@e
> 0>
>
> which puzzles me, because it looks like they are equal. But I am new
> to JUnit and I might not get it.
>
> Thank you,
> Benjamin
